# Arc: WarriorPath | Scene: WarriorQueen4ridgehaven
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah was standing at the entrance of the warcamp."
    new "Sarah was standing at the entrance of the warcamp."

    old "Kate had set out a day ago for the nearby city of Ridgehaven, taking command of the scouting group."
    new "Kate had set out a day ago for the nearby city of Ridgehaven, taking command of the scouting group."

    old "Sarah had been given the signal that Kate's scouting group had been seen returning."
    new "Sarah had been given the signal that Kate's scouting group had been seen returning."

    old "Anxiously, Sarah watched the scouts return from a distance."
    new "Anxiously, Sarah watched the scouts return from a distance."

    old "Dressed in dark cloaks, short one man, she worried most for Kate."
    new "Dressed in dark cloaks, short one man, she worried most for Kate."

    old "Please, let her be safe, Sarah prayed silently."
    new "Please, let her be safe, Sarah prayed silently."

    old "Finally, when the scout group was close enough, Sarah could see Kate at the lead."
    new "Finally, when the scout group was close enough, Sarah could see Kate at the lead."

    old "She sighed a beath of relief."
    new "She sighed a beath of relief."

    old "Kate rode quickly through the entrance of the camp and jumped off the horse."
    new "Kate rode quickly through the entrance of the camp and jumped off the horse."

    old "She'd always been a skilled rider, and the snow had done little to slow her down."
    new "She'd always been a skilled rider, and the snow had done little to slow her down."

    old "A small crowd had gathered to watch the arriving scouts, eager for news."
    new "A small crowd had gathered to watch the arriving scouts, eager for news."

    old "Kate strode across the open space towards Sarah, holding up a small piece of paper."
    new "Kate strode across the open space towards Sarah, holding up a small piece of paper."

    old "You lazy fucks can all go back to your jobs now, we made it."
    new "You lazy fucks can all go back to your jobs now, we made it."

    old "And this report is for her eyes only."
    new "And this report is for her eyes only."

    old "Kate gestured towards Sarah."
    new "Kate gestured towards Sarah."

    old "Behind Kate, the other scouts rode into the warcamp."
    new "Behind Kate, the other scouts rode into the warcamp."

    old "You're down a man. Did something happen?"
    new "You're down a man. Did something happen?"

    old "All good. Just had one man ride slow, make sure nobody was following us back to the camp."
    new "All good. Just had one man ride slow, make sure nobody was following us back to the camp."

    old "Sarah sighed a breath of relief again. The fewer deaths the better."
    new "Sarah sighed a breath of relief again. The fewer deaths the better."

    old "Good, what do you have to report?"
    new "Good, what do you have to report?"

    old "Kate gestured towards the tent."
    new "Kate gestured towards the tent."

    old "I can brief you, shall we do it in private?"
    new "I can brief you, shall we do it in private?"

    old "Sarah watched as the other scouts dismounted their horses."
    new "Sarah watched as the other scouts dismounted their horses."

    old "Scout\" \"Yeah, I bet."
    new "Scout\" \"Yeah, I bet."

    old "What's that?!"
    new "What's that?!"

    old "Kate turned about, clearly angry."
    new "Kate turned about, clearly angry."

    old "Scout\" \"Nothing. I just hope that report is full and complete."
    new "Scout\" \"Nothing. I just hope that report is full and complete."

    old "You got something to say, how about you just spit it out like a man?"
    new "You got something to say, how about you just spit it out like a man?"

    old "Sarah grabbed Kate by the arm."
    new "Sarah grabbed Kate by the arm."

    old "Sarah spoke quietly, yet firmly."
    new "Sarah spoke quietly, yet firmly."

    old "Just some ungrateful fuck that can't respect rank."
    new "Just some ungrateful fuck that can't respect rank."

    old "The scout spat on the ground."
    new "The scout spat on the ground."

    old "Scout\" \"Fuck rank. I didn't sign up for this. She almost got us killed!"
    new "Scout\" \"Fuck rank. I didn't sign up for this. She almost got us killed!"

    old "Sarah saw Kate was nearly ready to pull out her sword."
    new "Sarah saw Kate was nearly ready to pull out her sword."

    old "Grabbing Kate by the arm, she pulled her away."
    new "Grabbing Kate by the arm, she pulled her away."

    old "With me."
    new "With me."

    old "But Sarah, that-"
    new "But Sarah, that-"

    old "Now! This is not a request!"
    new "Now! This is not a request!"

    old "Sarah saw Kate's face flushed with rage, briefly, then she yielded."
    new "Sarah saw Kate's face flushed with rage, briefly, then she yielded."

    old "The two of them walked back to the command tent."
    new "The two of them walked back to the command tent."

    old "Report!"
    new "Report!"

    old "Sarah could hear her own voice booming."
    new "Sarah could hear her own voice booming."

    old "Kate was clearly unhappy at being ordered around so directly."
    new "Kate was clearly unhappy at being ordered around so directly."

    old "Are you going to explain yourself?"
    new "Are you going to explain yourself?"

    old "Kate held up the scroll."
    new "Kate held up the scroll."

    old "The report is here. You can read it, it's all in there."
    new "The report is here. You can read it, it's all in there."

    old "Sarah snatched the scroll from Kate's hand and threw it on the desk."
    new "Sarah snatched the scroll from Kate's hand and threw it on the desk."

    old "If I wanted to read the fucking report, I'd be reading it."
    new "If I wanted to read the fucking report, I'd be reading it."

    old "How about you sum it up for me in your own words."
    new "How about you sum it up for me in your own words."

    old "And it better explain why your men were acting the way they were."
    new "And it better explain why your men were acting the way they were."

    old "They can't respect rank."
    new "They can't respect rank."

    old "That's it? That's the story you want to go with?"
    new "That's it? That's the story you want to go with?"

    old "Because I can go and ask them, and if their story doesn't match up, we're going to be having a real problem."
    new "Because I can go and ask them, and if their story doesn't match up, we're going to be having a real problem."

    old "Fine, you want a report, you'll get it."
    new "Fine, you want a report, you'll get it."

    old "For a moment, she was quiet, gathering her thoughts."
    new "For a moment, she was quiet, gathering her thoughts."

    old "How am I going to put this..."
    new "How am I going to put this..."

    old "How about you begin at the start."
    new "How about you begin at the start."

    old "Kate leaned forward again."
    new "Kate leaned forward again."

    old "Well, we rode from camp and we got to Ridgehaven pretty easily."
    new "Well, we rode from camp and we got to Ridgehaven pretty easily."

    old "Only real issue was some heavy snowfall, but other than that, we made it there just fine."
    new "Only real issue was some heavy snowfall, but other than that, we made it there just fine."

    old "Sarah hadn't expected much else. The road to Ridgehaven had always been pretty safe. Uneventful."
    new "Sarah hadn't expected much else. The road to Ridgehaven had always been pretty safe. Uneventful."

    old "We get there, we make our way into town, and it's busy."
    new "We get there, we make our way into town, and it's busy."

    old "Some people look at us, but nothing more than a glance. You know, townfolk eyeing strangers, that sort of shit."
    new "Some people look at us, but nothing more than a glance. You know, townfolk eyeing strangers, that sort of shit."

    old "We make our way to the inn, it's bustling. Filled to the brim."
    new "We make our way to the inn, it's bustling. Filled to the brim."

    old "We set up in a corner, get some drinks-"
    new "We set up in a corner, get some drinks-"

    old "Kate frowned, annoyed at the interruption."
    new "Kate frowned, annoyed at the interruption."

    old "No, I didn't, but thanks for asking Mom."
    new "No, I didn't, but thanks for asking Mom."

    old "Can I finish the report?"
    new "Can I finish the report?"

    old "Sarah gestured at Kate to continue."
    new "Sarah gestured at Kate to continue."

    old "Anyway, we set up in the tavern, and we try to get some information. We spread out, talk to the townsfolk."
    new "Anyway, we set up in the tavern, and we try to get some information. We spread out, talk to the townsfolk."

    old "We pass off some bullshit about being traveling traders to avoid suspicion."
    new "We pass off some bullshit about being traveling traders to avoid suspicion."

    old "What did you discover?"
    new "What did you discover?"

    old "Nothing much."
    new "Nothing much."

    old "Most people hate the Tribesmen. The economy has gone to shit."
    new "Most people hate the Tribesmen. The economy has gone to shit."

    old "To shit?"
    new "To shit?"

    old "The Tribesmen don't know too much about farming and such."
    new "The Tribesmen don't know too much about farming and such."

    old "The only thing they seem to know is how to tax the locals."
    new "The only thing they seem to know is how to tax the locals."

    old "Well, they call it a tax, but there doesn't seem to be much of a rhyme or reason to it."
    new "Well, they call it a tax, but there doesn't seem to be much of a rhyme or reason to it."

    old "Well I mean that a Tribesmen just shows up and tells them they want something, and they call it a tax."
    new "Well I mean that a Tribesmen just shows up and tells them they want something, and they call it a tax."

    old "They tax em as much as they want or as often as they want."
    new "They tax em as much as they want or as often as they want."

    old "And supposedly, they let the townsfolk with pretty daughters pay in other ways."
    new "And supposedly, they let the townsfolk with pretty daughters pay in other ways."

    old "Did you get any trouble from asking these questions?"
    new "Did you get any trouble from asking these questions?"

    old "Not too much. The townsfolk and the Tribesmen seem to live pretty seperate."
    new "Not too much. The townsfolk and the Tribesmen seem to live pretty seperate."

    old "The Tribesmen are all up in a small fort in the center of town."
    new "The Tribesmen are all up in a small fort in the center of town."

    old "They drink, they feast, and that seems to be about all they do."
    new "They drink, they feast, and that seems to be about all they do."

    old "So they're disliked by the people?"
    new "So they're disliked by the people?"

    old "And...what about local leadership?"
    new "And...what about local leadership?"

    old "Kate smirked."
    new "Kate smirked."

    old "Funny you ask."
    new "Funny you ask."

    old "Funny how?"
    new "Funny how?"

    old "Well, that sort of brings us to the trouble with my men."
    new "Well, that sort of brings us to the trouble with my men."

    old "Explain."
    new "Explain."

    old "Kate sighed deeply."
    new "Kate sighed deeply."

    old "We talked to the locals in the tavern, and we slowly got a better picture of the town."
    new "We talked to the locals in the tavern, and we slowly got a better picture of the town."

    old "Who is who, all that."
    new "Who is who, all that."

    old "And like you said, I figured whose in charge of the town is probably something you care about."
    new "And like you said, I figured whose in charge of the town is probably something you care about."

    old "Figuring out who is colaborating with the Tribesmen."
    new "Figuring out who is colaborating with the Tribesmen."

    old "So, did you find out who it is?"
    new "So, did you find out who it is?"

    old "Fella named William Clay."
    new "Fella named William Clay."

    old "I don't know who that is. Am I supposed to?"
    new "I don't know who that is. Am I supposed to?"

    old "Don't mean nothing to you, but he means a little something to me."
    new "Don't mean nothing to you, but he means a little something to me."

    old "Well, I told you about when I ran away from home."
    new "Well, I told you about when I ran away from home."

    old "And I told you about drifting around Rosanna for a while, before I met up with Vaelen and the mercenary company."
    new "And I told you about drifting around Rosanna for a while, before I met up with Vaelen and the mercenary company."

    old "I remember."
    new "I remember."

    old "Well, Ridgehaven was one of the towns where I stayed for a while as I was drifting from place to place."
    new "Well, Ridgehaven was one of the towns where I stayed for a while as I was drifting from place to place."

    old "Sarah felt a surge of dread building in her stomach."
    new "Sarah felt a surge of dread building in her stomach."

    old "Oh, don't interrupt me now, Commander. You want the briefing, I'll give it to you."
    new "Oh, don't interrupt me now, Commander. You want the briefing, I'll give it to you."

    old "Sarah saw rage building in Kate's face."
    new "Sarah saw rage building in Kate's face."

    old "Good old William was a proper man of the people even back then. Ran a small little construction company."
    new "Good old William was a proper man of the people even back then. Ran a small little construction company."

    old "Good man. Honest man. Well respected about town."
    new "Good man. Honest man. Well respected about town."

    old "And when I showed up, he was more than eager to help me out."
    new "And when I showed up, he was more than eager to help me out."

    old "Give me a place to stay, up in a small room above the tavern."
    new "Give me a place to stay, up in a small room above the tavern."

    old "Give me some food, some coin, enough to survive."
    new "Give me some food, some coin, enough to survive."

    old "Sarah saw Kate's hands form into a fist."
    new "Sarah saw Kate's hands form into a fist."

    old "But by then I had gotten a little sharper to the world. The real world."
    new "But by then I had gotten a little sharper to the world. The real world."

    old "And I knew what men wanted from me."
    new "And I knew what men wanted from me."

    old "And by then I was starving, homeless and desperate enough that I had come to accept that bargain."
    new "And by then I was starving, homeless and desperate enough that I had come to accept that bargain."

    old "Nah, you wanted to know Sarah, so let's have it out."
    new "Nah, you wanted to know Sarah, so let's have it out."

    old "Up above that tavern, I got to be his little secret, while he walked about all of town like he was made of gold."
    new "Up above that tavern, I got to be his little secret, while he walked about all of town like he was made of gold."

    old "And everybody loved him, such a funny guy. So generous with this money. And so devout to his family. Front row in church, every week."
    new "And everybody loved him, such a funny guy. So generous with this money. And so devout to his family. Front row in church, every week."

    old "They didn't let me in the church, obviously, but I got to watch from my little room how he walked in there with all the others."
    new "They didn't let me in the church, obviously, but I got to watch from my little room how he walked in there with all the others."

    old "Sarah saw a wry smile on Kate's face."
    new "Sarah saw a wry smile on Kate's face."

    old "And I fucking thought I had it made."
    new "And I fucking thought I had it made."

    old "Wasn't homeless no more. Had food in me. Maybe if this was all I was good for, fine."
    new "Wasn't homeless no more. Had food in me. Maybe if this was all I was good for, fine."

    old "But you know, he and I didn't do much thinking up in that room, and his appetites were...frequent."
    new "But you know, he and I didn't do much thinking up in that room, and his appetites were...frequent."

    old "So it wasn't long before I missed a bleed, and even then I wasn't stupid enough not to know what that meant."
    new "So it wasn't long before I missed a bleed, and even then I wasn't stupid enough not to know what that meant."

    old "So I go visit William."
    new "So I go visit William."

    old "I tell him all about it."
    new "I tell him all about it."

    old "You shoulda seen me, shaking like a leaf, scared out my mind."
    new "You shoulda seen me, shaking like a leaf, scared out my mind."

    old "But he's all smiles."
    new "But he's all smiles."

    old "Tells me, we're gonna make a family, and he'll buy me my own big house on the countryside."
    new "Tells me, we're gonna make a family, and he'll buy me my own big house on the countryside."

    old "All he gotta do is make some preparations, move some money around, and I can meet up with him at the end of the week to go there."
    new "All he gotta do is make some preparations, move some money around, and I can meet up with him at the end of the week to go there."

    old "Kate laughed, even as Sarah saw the tears forming in Kate's eyes."
    new "Kate laughed, even as Sarah saw the tears forming in Kate's eyes."

    old "Stupid as a mule, I show up in the dead of night in the alley behind the tavern where we had agreed to meet."
    new "Stupid as a mule, I show up in the dead of night in the alley behind the tavern where we had agreed to meet."

    old "Waiting for the cart to take me to my little dream house."
    new "Waiting for the cart to take me to my little dream house."

    old "And just like we agreed, William was waiting for me. Him and two of his friends."
    new "And just like we agreed, William was waiting for me. Him and two of his friends."

    old "William's a big fella, but his two friends were even bigger."
    new "William's a big fella, but his two friends were even bigger."

    old "He smiles and says he's real sorry about all of this."
    new "He smiles and says he's real sorry about all of this."

    old "I ask what he's sorry about, but then his friends grab me and get to work on me."
    new "I ask what he's sorry about, but then his friends grab me and get to work on me."

    old "For the better part of an hour, the three of them take their turns holding me down, stomping me in the stomach."
    new "For the better part of an hour, the three of them take their turns holding me down, stomping me in the stomach."

    old "They hold back my head and pour more drink down my throat than I've ever gotten down before or after."
    new "They hold back my head and pour more drink down my throat than I've ever gotten down before or after."

    old "Then some more beating."
    new "Then some more beating."

    old "By some point, either the beating or the drink, I was so out of it, I don't know what was up or down."
    new "By some point, either the beating or the drink, I was so out of it, I don't know what was up or down."

    old "Only the punches...those I could count like clockwork."
    new "Only the punches...those I could count like clockwork."

    old "Kate looked up at Sarah, tears streaming down her face."
    new "Kate looked up at Sarah, tears streaming down her face."

    old "They left me there, satisfied that by now whatever had been growing in me was surely dead."
    new "They left me there, satisfied that by now whatever had been growing in me was surely dead."

    old "I was lying on the ground...when I lost consciousness, I have no idea..."
    new "I was lying on the ground...when I lost consciousness, I have no idea..."

    old "Sarah tried to reach out, but Kate flinched."
    new "Sarah tried to reach out, but Kate flinched."

    old "I woke up the next day with bruises all over my body. Skin as purple as grapes."
    new "I woke up the next day with bruises all over my body. Skin as purple as grapes."

    old "My spot in the tavern, gone. The money I had saved up, gone."
    new "My spot in the tavern, gone. The money I had saved up, gone."

    old "When next I saw him in town, he walked straight past me. Didn't even glance."
    new "When next I saw him in town, he walked straight past me. Didn't even glance."

    old "I thought about confronting him...but knowing what he had done, what he was capeable of doing...I didn't think confronting him would be a good idea."
    new "I thought about confronting him...but knowing what he had done, what he was capeable of doing...I didn't think confronting him would be a good idea."

    old "He was well liked, respectable. I was little more than a homeless whore."
    new "He was well liked, respectable. I was little more than a homeless whore."

    old "So I left."
    new "So I left."

    old "Took me a few days, but then I got out of town, on to the next..."
    new "Took me a few days, but then I got out of town, on to the next..."

    old "I met Vaelen not long after."
    new "I met Vaelen not long after."

    old "Sarah looked at her friend, rare to show any emotion, now ruined with it."
    new "Sarah looked at her friend, rare to show any emotion, now ruined with it."

    old "Kate...what happened in Ridgehaven?"
    new "Kate...what happened in Ridgehaven?"

    old "Kate wiped away some of the tears on her face. Tried grounding herself again."
    new "Kate wiped away some of the tears on her face. Tried grounding herself again."

    old "She cleared her throat as she continued to speak."
    new "She cleared her throat as she continued to speak."

    old "Well, like I said...we learned that he had been made Mayor in the years after."
    new "Well, like I said...we learned that he had been made Mayor in the years after."

    old "The previous Mayor seemed less cooperative with the Tribesmen, and so they drowned him in the fountain in the town's square."
    new "The previous Mayor seemed less cooperative with the Tribesmen, and so they drowned him in the fountain in the town's square."

    old "The Tribesmen supposedly killed their way through a good few men before they found one that was willing to bend for them."
    new "The Tribesmen supposedly killed their way through a good few men before they found one that was willing to bend for them."

    old "William."
    new "William."

    old "Weak enough to be their puppet. Liked enough by the townsfolk to be taken serious."
    new "Weak enough to be their puppet. Liked enough by the townsfolk to be taken serious."

    old "That's it."
    new "That's it."

    old "A man like that goes about life, lying, cheating."
    new "A man like that goes about life, lying, cheating."

    old "He doesn't have a shred of loyalty or integrity to him, and he gets to be the Mayor of a town?"
    new "He doesn't have a shred of loyalty or integrity to him, and he gets to be the Mayor of a town?"

    old "He gets rewarded for everything he's ever done?"
    new "He gets rewarded for everything he's ever done?"

    old "What did you do?"
    new "What did you do?"

    old "I went out and I set things right."
    new "I went out and I set things right."

    old "Kate looked up, her eyes furious."
    new "Kate looked up, her eyes furious."

    old "That's what we came here to do, right? To restore this country. To make it right again!"
    new "That's what we came here to do, right? To restore this country. To make it right again!"

    old "Or did we just come here to get you a throne?"
    new "Or did we just come here to get you a throne?"

    old "Sarah looked at her friend, shaking with a mixture of anger and sadness."
    new "Sarah looked at her friend, shaking with a mixture of anger and sadness."

    old "You killed him?"
    new "You killed him?"

    old "Snuck into his big fat mansion in the center of town and stabbed him to death in his bed."
    new "Snuck into his big fat mansion in the center of town and stabbed him to death in his bed."

    old "He screamed like a pig as he died. Fitting."
    new "He screamed like a pig as he died. Fitting."

    old "Did you know this when you asked for the mission?"
    new "Did you know this when you asked for the mission?"

    old "Kate looked at her."
    new "Kate looked at her."

    old "She said nothing."
    new "She said nothing."

    old "I knew he lived there. I remembered that."
    new "I knew he lived there. I remembered that."

    old "Did I go there just to kill him...I don't..."
    new "Did I go there just to kill him...I don't..."

    old "Kate's voiced drifted."
    new "Kate's voiced drifted."

    old "I don't think so..."
    new "I don't think so..."

    old "You don't think so?"
    new "You don't think so?"

    old "No...I can't remember when I decided to do it..."
    new "No...I can't remember when I decided to do it..."

    old "Kate...I understand why you did it...but the Tribesmen will be on alert now."
    new "Kate...I understand why you did it...but the Tribesmen will be on alert now."

    old "The Mayor was murdered...strangers in the town the night before...they'll start looking around."
    new "The Mayor was murdered...strangers in the town the night before...they'll start looking around."

    old "We wanted to keep a low profile...now..."
    new "We wanted to keep a low profile...now..."

    old "Fuck...I mean...I didn't think it through that far. I just wanted to kill the fuck."
    new "Fuck...I mean...I didn't think it through that far. I just wanted to kill the fuck."

    old "If you..."
    new "If you..."

    old "Kate's voice went soft."
    new "Kate's voice went soft."

    old "If you have to punish me, I get it. disobedience."
    new "If you have to punish me, I get it. disobedience."

    old "I'm not asking for special favors."
    new "I'm not asking for special favors."

    old "Looking at her friend, Sarah was of two minds."
    new "Looking at her friend, Sarah was of two minds."

    old "One part of her cared for her friend, and was glad she got her vengeance."
    new "One part of her cared for her friend, and was glad she got her vengeance."

    old "The other part of her was loyal to her army. Her cause. And Kate's revenge, however just, had threatend her campaign when it had only just begun."
    new "The other part of her was loyal to her army. Her cause. And Kate's revenge, however just, had threatend her campaign when it had only just begun."

    old "If she let Kate get away with it...what would that signal to the others?"
    new "If she let Kate get away with it...what would that signal to the others?"

    old "Then again...didn't she have a loyalty to her friend? Could she punish her for killing a man who so dearly deserved it?"
    new "Then again...didn't she have a loyalty to her friend? Could she punish her for killing a man who so dearly deserved it?"

    old "Punish Kate"
    new "Punish Kate"

    old "Sarah knew what had to be done."
    new "Sarah knew what had to be done."

    old "You know I can't just let you walk away from this without any punishment."
    new "You know I can't just let you walk away from this without any punishment."

    old "You endangered this entire campaign, all because of a personal grievance."
    new "You endangered this entire campaign, all because of a personal grievance."

    old "However just...I can't let such disobedience stand."
    new "However just...I can't let such disobedience stand."

    old "Not even from you. Not even from a friend."
    new "Not even from you. Not even from a friend."

    old "Kate lowered her head."
    new "Kate lowered her head."

    old "She slowly nodded."
    new "She slowly nodded."

    old "I understand..."
    new "I understand..."

    old "Sarah hated how cold Kate was."
    new "Sarah hated how cold Kate was."

    old "But she also understood the difference that now existed between them."
    new "But she also understood the difference that now existed between them."

    old "They were friends, but before that, she was a ruler and Kate a servant."
    new "They were friends, but before that, she was a ruler and Kate a servant."

    old "Sarah had tried all her life to forget that fact. Now she could no longer deny it."
    new "Sarah had tried all her life to forget that fact. Now she could no longer deny it."

    old "On Sarah's orders, the guards took Kate away."
    new "On Sarah's orders, the guards took Kate away."

    old "Tied to a pole, the guards delivered five lashes, one for each scout that she had endangered with her actions."
    new "Tied to a pole, the guards delivered five lashes, one for each scout that she had endangered with her actions."

